13:
Ohio / West Virginia, 1896-1912...

Caption
This photograph of three women and two men posed in a yard near a wood swing was taken by traveling photographer Albert J. Ewing, ca. 1896-1912. Behind them is a large, steep grassy hillside. One of the women is identified on the negative as Judith Ruckman, but the others are unidentified. Like most of Ewing's work, the photograph was likely taken in the region of southeastern Ohio and central West Virginia...

Source
Ohio History Connection
